  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "When a transaction is sent with a nonce that has already been used, geth returns [\"nonce too low\"](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/f32feeb260054d7c90c1efd57dfec6b717717e18/core/error.go#L48) whereas hardhat network returns [\"None too low\"](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/bf48f1c98ada6bb7ffafd7116dea265471dd9525/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts#L1686)\r\n\r\nThis causes an error in ethers-rs' [EscalatingPending](https://docs.rs/ethers-providers/0.6.2/src/ethers_providers/pending_escalator.rs.html#145) code. Admitedly this is a bad way to filter for errors, but is there a reason why hardhat network is not following geth's convention?\r\n",
